Abstract: This report gives a broad sketch of American practices in the organization, administration, and financing of applied research in the natural sciences and engineering.  Also highlighted are the ways in which new results found in the research laboratory are communicated to those responsible for their practical utilization.  The report is directed mainly toward administrators of research in governments and industries of other countries.  Fixed limitations on length as well as the needs of a non-technical audience unfamiliar with American ways have led us to simplify the presentation.  Thus many general statements are made without the exceptions and qualifications a more complete account would contain.  (Author abstract, modified)
